";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Eric Knott";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1712:"<p>Not so long ago, the French connection at Celtic was similar to the Japanese connection we&#8217;ve had over the last three years or so.</p>
<p>During Brendan Rodgers&#8217; first stint at the club, we had Moussa Dembele, Olivier Ntcham, and Odsonne Edouard.</p>
<p>Not long after that, we had Christopher Jullien join the club. He will always be remembered for his strike against Lazio in the Europa League in October of 2019.</p>
<p>Sadly, since Ange Postecoglou&#8217;s time at Celtic, followed by Brendan Rodgers&#8217; second stint, we have had no French players of note join the club since Chris Jullien left.</p>
<p>One thing we can say for sure is that all of the French contingent that played at Celtic during Brendan Rodgers&#8217; time achieved great things.</p>
<p>Who can forget Moussa Dembele&#8217;s goal at Ibrox, followed by Odsonne Edouard&#8217;s sublime finish to win at Ibrox with ten men this time seven years ago?</p>
<p>Isn&#8217;t it ironic that Sunday&#8217;s game at Celtic Park is the first game where more than 800 fans have been allowed to attend after the Ibrox side threw their toys out of the pram after that famous win?</p>
<p>Let&#8217;s hope we give the 2,600 Ibrox fans at Celtic Park on Sunday a game to remember.</p>
<p>For all the wrong reasons.</p>
