";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Eric Knott";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6545:"<p>Days after another share issue, and an &#8220;<a href="https://readceltic.com/2025/03/12/celtic-could-land-as-much-as-10-2-million-from-the-sale-of-jeremie-frimpong-while-the-ibrox-side-are-borrowing-money-to-cover-future-transfer-income/">unspecified</a>&#8221; loan amount taken out against future transfer income, operation sell Hamza Igamane for megabucks is under way.</p>
<p>Now, I think it&#8217;s safe to say Igamane may have been in the shop window about 6 weeks ago, but he has been experiencing a pretty barren spell since his prolific scoring spree around Christmas time.</p>
<p>Nonetheless, that hasn&#8217;t deterred Sevilla from declaring interest in the Moroccan hit man.</p>
<p>According to the <a href="https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-transfer-news/hamza-igamane-set-84m-sevilla-34852054">Record</a> this morning, Sevilla are &#8220;preparing&#8221; a bid of £8.4 million for the Moroccan superstar.</p>
<p>The source of this amazing story?</p>
<h3 id="h-well-it-appears-to-be-from-a-blogger-who-just-as-i-blog-about-celtic-blogs-about-sevilla" class="wp-block-heading">Well, it appears to be from a blogger who, just as I blog about Celtic, blogs about Sevilla.</h3>
<p><img decoding="async" title="Rangers FC v St Mirren FC - William Hill Premiership" src="https://cdn.readeverything.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/39/2025/03/2201293594.jpg" alt="Rob Casey - SNS Group/SNS Group/Getty Images" data-portal-copyright="Rob Casey - SNS Group/SNS Group/Getty Images" data-image="8oi8dttjysea" /></p>
<p>The site is called <a href="https://www.vamosmisevillafc.com/el-futurible-delantero-del-sevilla-eleva-su-cache/">SAMOSSEVILLA</a>, and as I do here at Read Celtic, it discusses all things Sevilla related.</p>
<p>You know?</p>
<p>Transfer rumours, club news, etc. etc.</p>
<p>I would never claim to be a credible source for the Scottish Mainstream Sports Media, nor would I ever expect the SMSM to use my work as a source for theirs.</p>
<p>On the contrary, I would be offended if they did, considering they often use Football Insider as a source.</p>
<p>For me to be as much as associated with a site like that, well, I would find that highly offensive!</p>
<p>You can rest assured the SMSM would never use my site as a source.</p>
<h3 id="h-that-would-be-anathema-to-them-as-i-am-a-celtic-site-that-continuously-calls-out-their-bullshit-and-shoddy-journalism" class="wp-block-heading">That would be anathema to them, as my site is a Celtic site that continuously calls out their bullshit and shoddy journalism.</h3>
<p>Which is ironically what I&#8217;m doing right now.</p>
<p>Robbie Copeland has gone looking for a story and found one in the Spanish blogosphere.</p>
<p>He has used a site that doesn&#8217;t even have an author&#8217;s name on it with the titled credited to &#8220;vmscom&#8221;.</p>
<p>So there&#8217;s nobody who can actually be contacted to verify this story.</p>
<p>Below is the literal translation of the story:</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Sevilla&#8217;s potential striker is increasing his cachet</h3>
<p>March 12, 2025 by <a href="https://www.vamosmisevillafc.com/author/vmscom/">vmscom</a></p>
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote"><p><em>Víctor Orta&#8217;s biggest pending issue at Sevilla FC, since his arrival two summers ago, is acquiring a striker who at least scores goals.</em></p>
<p><em>As we&#8217;ve already mentioned, while waiting for the possible signing of Akor Adams, who is in his final phase of recovery, he has another potential striker in mind for next year.</em></p>
<p><em>This is Hamza Igamane, a 21-year-old Moroccan striker for Glasgow Rangers, who is breaking out this season with 13 goals and 3 assists in 35 matches, drawing comparisons from many to former Atletico player and compatriot Youseff En-Nesyri.</em></p>
<p><em>He will be playing alongside the former Sevilla player in two very upcoming matches: the second leg of the Europa League round of 16, with the Scots leading 3-1, and the call-up to Morocco for this international break.</em></p>
<p><em>This is the Scottish team&#8217;s first call-up for the striker, which will further boost his stature ahead of the upcoming summer transfer window.</em></p>
<p><em>Valued at 2.5 million by Transfermarkt, we already reported this week that Sevilla were preparing an initial offer of 10 million, which could fall short if the young striker continues to reach levels like those with his national team.</em></p></blockquote>
<p>Now, if you&#8217;ve read that, can you honestly tell me that this piece is written by a creditable source who has inside knowledge of transfers at Sevilla?</p>
<p>It is a blog.</p>
<p>And it is pure speculation.</p>
<p>No more, no less.</p>
<p>The SMSM are attempting to put Igamane in the shop window.</p>
<h3 id="h-the-same-way-they-attempted-to-put-alfredo-morelos-in-the-shop-window-back-in-2017-with-the-mystery-7-5-million-bid-from-china" class="wp-block-heading">The same way they attempted to put Alfredo Morelos in the shop window back in 2017, with the mystery £7.5 million bid from China.</h3>
<p><img decoding="async" title="Rangers v Heart of Midlothian - Cinch Premiership" src="https://cdn.readeverything.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/39/2025/03/1258323498.jpg" alt="Rob Casey - SNS Group/SNS Group/Getty Images" data-portal-copyright="Rob Casey - SNS Group/SNS Group/Getty Images" data-image="v789kwjhbzk9" /></p>
<p>This smacks of the exact same thing.</p>
<p>The exact same kind of desperation.</p>
<p>On a week where the continued financial difficulties of the Ibrox club have once again been laid bare, isn&#8217;t it a coincidence that a story such as this then appears?</p>
<p>Well, Igamane would want to be rediscovering his scoring touch in order for anyone to be showing interest in him.</p>
<p>I guess he&#8217;ll have the perfect opportunity on Sunday to do that.</p>
<p>And if he does, his value will increase from £8.4 million to £14 million.</p>
<p>Just like that.</p>
<p>A Sevilla blogger&#8230;</p>
<p>You couldn&#8217;t make it up.</p>
<p>These people really do steal a wage at times.</p>
<p>It was ever thus.</p>
