<p>The post <a href="https://readceltic.com/2025/03/11/the-record-go-all-out-football-insider-with-expert-opinion-from-phil-bardsley-who-on-how-bazza-will-beat-brendan-rodgers-and-celtic/">The Record go all out Football Insider with &#8220;expert opinion&#8221; from Phil Bardsley (who??) on how Bazza will beat Brendan Rodgers and Celtic!!</a> appeared first on <a href="https://readceltic.com">Read Celtic</a>.</p>
";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Eric Knott";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8029:"<p>Phil Bardsley, yeah, anybody remember that guy?</p>
<p>Anybody ever remember him playing for Rangers 1872?</p>
<p>Because I don&#8217;t.</p>
<p>Apparently, a guy who played only 5 times back in 2006 for the deid club while on loan from Manchester United, is in a position to tell us that Bazza is going to own Brendan Rodgers in next Sunday&#8217;s Glasgow Derby.</p>
<p>In fact, Bardsley believes the Ibrox side are 10 times, YES, 10 times more likely to do the business against Celtic than they were under Philippe Clement.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m not sure you can put a number on something like that, but Bardsley has given it a shot.</p>
<p>In true Football Insider style reportage, the <a href="https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/former-rangers-star-bullish-celtic-34840066">Record</a> has decided to pluck the opinion of a &#8220;former R*****s star&#8221; out of thin air.</p>
<p>I guess if you played just 5 times for them, that must make you a &#8220;former star&#8221; then?</p>
<p>According to the headline in Record, it does anyway:</p>
<p><strong><em>Former Rangers star in bullish Celtic clash prediction as Barry Ferguson told where he&#8217;s TEN times better than Clement</em></strong></p>
<p>You read a headline like that, and you just shake your head.</p>
<p>What next?</p>
<p>Former Celtic Superstar Rafael Scheidt predicts Brendan Rodgers will lord over &#8220;rookie&#8221; Barry Ferguson in O** F*** Derby?</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-in-even-more-true-football-insider-style-expert-bardsley-is-predicting-that-frank-lampard-will-get-the-ibrox-job">In even more true Football Insider style, &#8220;expert&#8221; Bardsley is predicting that Frank Lampard will get the Ibrox job.</h3>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.readeverything.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/39/2025/03/2203538850.jpg" alt="Stephen White - CameraSport/CameraSport/Getty Images" title="Coventry City FC v Stoke City FC - Sky Bet Championship" data-portal-copyright="Stephen White - CameraSport/CameraSport/Getty Images" data-image="3ef1ns30wfvx"></p>
<p>Here are the opening paragraphs to this masterpiece:</p>
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">
<p>Rangers are TEN times more likely to do the business against&nbsp;<a href="https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/all-about/celtic-fc">Celtic</a>&nbsp;than they were under Philippe Clement, now Barry Ferguson has the reins.</p>
<p>That&#8217;s the view of ex-Gers defender Phil Bardsley, who also doesn&#8217;t think the door is fully closed on&nbsp;<a href="https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/all-about/frank-lampard">Frank Lampard</a>&nbsp;getting the permanent job.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well, I guess Bardsley wants Bazza to win the derby, but he doesn&#8217;t want him to get the job?</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s what former Ibrox 5 game hero Bardsley had to say about Bazza&#8217;s chances:</p>
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">
<p>Barry Ferguson is a huge character and he knows the club inside out, he has got the call to take the reins of the team and I think the players have the utmost respect for him.</p>
<p>They have that respect thanks to his achievements at the club and I think his character is a perfect fit for the club. There will be a transition period after Philippe Clement left, but they have gone back to basics and recent performances look to give them a ten times better chance in the O** F*** Derby against Celtic.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I&#8217;m guessing that Phil got to know Bazza well during his 5 game stint at Ibrox back in the day.</p>
<p>Or more to the point, Bazza behavioural characteristics.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-after-a-bit-of-research-i-discovered-bardsley-was-also-a-naughty-boy-at-ibrox-during-the-ill-fated-paul-le-guen-experiment">After a bit of research, I discovered Bardsley was also a naughty boy at Ibrox during the ill-fated Paul le Guen experiment.</h3>
<p>He had a training ground bust-up with Le Guen, and was sent packing back to Manchester not long after.</p>
<p>A month later, Bazza of course, was stripped of the captaincy by Le Guen.</p>
<p>So I guess that Bazza and Phil were a bit of a thorn in Le Guen&#8217;s side back in 2006.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.readeverything.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/39/2025/03/1278116383-1.jpg" alt="SNS Group/SNS Group/Getty Images" title="22/12/06 .Rangers Training .Murray Park - Glasgow.Frozen Out Rangers Defender Phil Bardsley, On Loan From Manchester Utd, Continues To Train With The Squad In The Hope Of A Return To The First Team" data-portal-copyright="SNS Group/SNS Group/Getty Images" data-image="80p3nc4xe2m9"></p>
<p>That&#8217;s how Bardsley knows that Bazza knows the club &#8220;inside out&#8221;.</p>
<p>For some strange reason though, Bardsley is touting Frank Lampard for the Ibrox job, and not Bazza:</p>
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">
<p>Stranger things have happened in football than Frank Lampard going to R*****s. Frank had a tough time at Chelsea after Everton and some critics almost seemed to write him off, but since he has gone to Coventry he has been absolutely incredible and it just goes to show what can happen when you find that right fit.</p>
<p>You are never too far from finding that fit and sometimes it just takes the right club and the right players buying into the philosophy. When it comes to Lampard and R*****s, you just never know in football, that’s the beauty of it, not knowing what to expect next. But I’m delighted with his season so far because he is a really good guy.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>All this speculation is very exciting, isn&#8217;t it?</p>
<p>With Coventry City in fifth place in the EFL Championship, and occupying the play-off places, there&#8217;s a chance they could make the EPL this season.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-i-m-sure-frank-lampard-would-be-off-to-ibrox-if-he-managed-to-pull-off-a-feat-like-that">I&#8217;m sure Frank Lampard would be off to Ibrox if he managed to pull off a feat like that.</h3>
<p>Indeed.</p>
<p>The SMSM is just delighted to present these wonderful puff pieces to keep the gullibillies happy.</p>
<p>While they conveniently ignore that there was another £5.3 million emergency share issue yesterday.</p>
<p>Now one does wonder what really is going on while the Yanks are doing their due dilligence?</p>
<p>I mean I know they&#8217;re loaded and everything, but surely they&#8217;ll be wondering why they&#8217;ll have to pay whoever had these shares converted another £5.3 million on top of what they&#8217;re going to have to pay already?</p>
<p>To find out more about this story, you can read it over on <a href="https://videocelts.com/2025/03/blogs/latest-news/rangers-international-share-issue/">VideoCelts</a>.</p>
<p>Joe McHugh really explains it all rather well.</p>
<p>Such inconvenient truths are kept away from those poor bears.</p>
<p>They don&#8217;t need to be reading things like that.</p>
<p>They&#8217;re in such a lofty position now, they can scoff at the idea of Jose Mourinho managing their club.</p>
<p>Cuz he&#8217;s shite, y&#8217;know?</p>
<p>They&#8217;ve proven that to the world.</p>
<p>By being world beaters again, of course.</p>
<p>Poor Celtic are in for it on Sunday.</p>
<p>You know, because now Bazza&#8217;s side is TEN times better than Phil Clement&#8217;s?</p>
<p>What a difference a couple of weeks makes!</p>
